&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Baron Capital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Baron Capital is a leading asset management firm founded in 1982. We believe that hiring, retaining, and nurturing talented individuals who share our passion for excellence, integrity, and innovation is the key to our success. This means creating a welcoming, inclusive, and inspiring environment for all, as well as providing the resources and support our employees need to succeed. We take pride in our exceptionally low turnover and consider it a testament to our culture of collaboration and open communication. If you are looking for a career where you are part of a dynamic team where you can truly make a difference, we invite you to consider joining us.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Regional Director is a driven and committed sales professional.&amp;nbsp; The Regional Director will be responsible for cultivating and maintaining relationships within the RIA channel as well as Bank Trust organizations and Single and Multi-Family Offices, delivering our growth equity strategies to these distribution channels. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Regional Director should be able to provide value-added support in a consultative manner according to individual advisor needs for our RIA &amp;amp; Family Office West territory. This includes the ability to have in-depth conversations about our products and the investment environment and experience in the sales approach appropriate and specific to these channels. The Regional Director will be charged with all sales and client relationships for the territory and will work with an assigned hybrid wholesaler as a territory partner. &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;u&gt;West:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/em&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;This territory includes (subject to change) California, Oregon, Washington, Nevada, Alaska, and Hawaii. Target locations are the San Francisco or Los Angeles Metropolitan areas, as these are the key business hubs and provide the best access to travel throughout the territory.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delivering our investment process and philosophy and demonstrating the uniqueness of each product&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrating a high degree of performance and ethics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing all stages of the sales cycle, from prospecting to discovery to implementation, as well as ongoing management of the relationship once established&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working well both as an individual and a member of a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Articulating strategies and how they relate to an individual or firm’s overall strategy and investment needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delivering advanced sales presentations on Baron Capital’s portfolios and strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have the ability to travel extensively (up to 75% of the time) with a high degree of accountability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Documenting and significant use of Salesforce.com&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Education/Experience: &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 3 years external financial services sales experience specific to the RIA channel, with a high degree of demonstrated success&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree a MUST, Master’s degree and/or CFA a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have Series 7 and 63&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Existing coverage of a large part of this territory with existing relationships a significant plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of the financial markets and ability to articulate accordingly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Knowledge and Skills:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated high level of performance and results in a recent/prior and similar financial sales role&lt;/li&

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Baron Capital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Baron Capital is a leading asset management firm founded in 1982. We believe that hiring, retaining, and nurturing talented individuals who share our passion for excellence, integrity, and innovation is the key to our success. This means creating a welcoming, inclusive, and inspiring environment for all, as well as providing the resources and support our employees need to succeed. We take pride in our exceptionally low turnover and consider it a testament to our culture of collaboration and open communication. If you are looking for a career where you are part of a dynamic team where you can truly make a difference, we invite you to consider joining us.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Research Assistant, you will directly support the Portfolio Manager(s) and Research Analysts on your team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your primary duties and responsibilities include&amp;nbsp;providing administrative support to ensure efficient operation of the office. You will support analysts and/or portfolio managers through a variety of tasks, including but not limited to: scheduling meetings, researching conferences, booking travel &amp;amp; making itineraries, creating and submitting expense reports, arranging conference calls, maintaining current watchlists as well as new ideas on FactSet for portfolios and companies your PM/analyst cover or are interested in researching, ordering catering, keeping contacts up to date, obtaining and filing company information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This individual will report directly to the VP, Director of Workplace Operations.&amp;nbsp; This team is comprised of 13 Research Assistants. The role will also involve coverage for other research assistants when needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Answer phone calls with proper call screening, forwarding, and message taking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Schedule meetings and appointments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with all necessary parties and gather all requested materials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with the receptionist to make sure the calendar appointment has all of the necessary details, such as attendee names, agenda, conference room, catering requests, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;When scheduling meetings with multiples analysts and PM’s must be able to work efficiently with other assistants&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sort through emails and search for relevant events, meetings or calls that may be of interest&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Check for relevant conferences and present the information to the analysts/PMs; keep track of deadlines and ensure registration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a liaison with brokers, banks and investor relations representative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with brokers and IR representatives to register PM’s/Analysts for Conferences and Investor Days and schedule any meetings that PM’s/Analysts find of interest.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make sure PM’s Analysts have the most current agenda for Conference and Investor Day and add any presentations to calendar that they would like to attend.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and update contact lists&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create or update documents and spreadsheets to help your analyst/PM streamline and organize his or her workload&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce and distribute correspondence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the preparation of regularly scheduled reports&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a filing system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Every quarter, keep track of the calendar for earnings calls.&amp;nbsp; This may include providing press releases, transcripts, estimates and research reports to your analysts/PMs in a timely fashion. This is done using Factset and or Bloomberg&lt;/li&

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Baron Capital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Baron Capital is a leading asset management firm founded in 1982. We believe that hiring, retaining, and nurturing talented individuals who share our passion for excellence, integrity, and innovation is the key to our success. This means creating a welcoming, inclusive, and inspiring environment for all, as well as providing the resources and support our employees need to succeed. We take pride in our exceptionally low turnover and consider it a testament to our culture of collaboration and open communication. If you are looking for a career where you are part of a dynamic team where you can truly make a difference, we invite you to consider joining us.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Sales Analyst supports the sales and distribution organization, specifically the Intermediary Sales Team, by ensuring the team has the tools, data, and insights needed to operate efficiently and grow and retain assets. The role sits at the intersection of sales support, CRM ownership, and sales data analytics, partnering closely with internal and external sales professionals, marketing, strategy &amp;amp; sales enablement, and leadership teams to maintain data integrity, build reporting, and grow and retain assets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is highly detailed-oriented, analytically minded, and passionate about building scalable processes that help sales teams perform at a higher level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the Salesforce CRM platform for the Intermediary Sales Team, including cleaning and maintaining CRM data integrity, supporting team campaigns, and supporting broader firm sales initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain CRM and accurate client contact information, and track engagement and activity across various wealth partner platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support team leadership by analyzing and maintaining key territory metrics, tracking wholesaler activity, and other management metrics providing clear, data driven insights that inform day-to-day management needs and support broader strategic decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and deliver reporting and analytics for sales campaigns, including generating targeted client lists, building, and structuring campaign outreach, and providing data‑driven insights for sales leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support external and internal sales efforts and financial advisor coverage such as assisting with literature fulfillment requests, Morningstar report portal comparisons, and ad hoc client requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally with teams such as the Strategy &amp;amp; Sales Enablement Team, National Accounts, and Marketing teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with ad hoc Intermediary Team and other department requests sent to dedicated Sales Analyst inbox&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the Investment Specialists, including attending weekly meetings andparticipating in presentation workshops&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend in-office firm events, meetings, and investment forums&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;After 12 months, potential sponsorship for the FINRA Series 7 &amp;amp; 63 exams/licensing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Required:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Undergraduate degree, preferably in finance, business, or economics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self‑motivated team player who is comfortable working in a fast‑paced environment, managing multiple tasks, and adapting to shifting priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for sales and knowledge of financial markets and basic economic principles&lt;/li&gt;
